WRITING.TITLE: [TOMT] Comic - Humans continue to grow throughout their lives.
WRITING.TEXT: The author/narrator was kept up late at night (I think by a barking dog) and imagined a world where humans continued to grow throughout their lives like lizards. There are many sections to it, about how society would have to adapt, to people living in different scales. A notable panel of him talking to his enormous grandfather. And how at the end of their lives the elderly are sent out into the wilderness to die. I saw it on Imgur once, and remember liking it.
